==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Limonite
<hw>Li"mon*ite</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧"m⟦ocr⟧n*⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>leimw`n</grk> any moist grassy place, a meadow: cf. F.
<ets>limonite</ets>, G. <ets>limonit</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>Hydrous sesquioxide of iron, an important ore of iron, occurring in
stalactitic, mammillary, or earthy forms, of a dark brown color, and
yellowish brown powder. It includes bog iron. Also called <altname>brown
hematite</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Limosis</ent>⟦br⟧
